==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Linden
<hw>Lin"den</hw> <pr>(l⟦icr⟧n"d⟦eit⟧n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Orig.
an adj. from <ets>lind</ets> linden tree, AS. <ets>lind</ets>; akin to
D. & G. <ets>linde</ets>, OHG. <ets>linta</ets>, Icel., Sw., & Dan.
<ets>lind</ets>. Cf. <er>Lime</er> linden.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<sd>(a)</sd> <def>A handsome tree (<spn>Tilia Europ⟦ae⟧a</spn>), having
cymes of light yellow flowers, and large cordate leaves. The tree is
common in Europe.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>In America, the basswood, or
<spn>Tilia Americana</spn>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lindera</ent>⟦br⟧
